tweets.text:
Securing the border is not enough.

You can lock down the entire house — lock every door, seal every window, and make sure no one else ever gets in again — but if you’ve already got an unknown number of strangers inside who broke in without your permission, your house is not secure.

They’re already here. They’re already living under your roof, eating your food, using your resources, and you have no idea how many there are or what they intend.

A locked house with intruders inside is not a fortress.
It’s a trap. The same is true for our nation.

We can build the wall, shut down the loopholes, and stop the invasion at the border — but until we find and remove every single person who entered America illegally, our country is not secure.

True sovereignty isn’t just about keeping new people out. It’s about removing those who never had the right to be here in the first place.

